714874f-a.title: Manhattan: 96th Street (East) - 2nd Avenue
714874f-a.text:
E. 96th Street, west from Second Avenue, showing buildings
on the south side of this thoroughfare. Note the upgrade that
reaches its peak at Park Avenue. Overhead is the Second Avenue
''El''. Former tenements at the N.W. corner of Second Avenue and
96th Street have been demolished and a sion erected there. The
photographer is standing in front of the car barn and viewing south-
weStward.
September 14, 1938.
P.L. Sperr
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
